{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"meMrNQ9iwLOCyjmsP39M2S6KY6k=","kind":"spec","title":"Design: `kref show` — header table, terminal width, line numbers, vim jumps","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"AZf/jDBka8CzmrvUnFN2IKv6ymg=","body":"# Design: `kref show` — header table, terminal width, line numbers, vim jumps\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-29\n**Branch:** feat/show-rendering-pager\n**Status:** approved (brainstorming)\n\n## Problem\n\n`kref show` renders an entry's header as a single dense inline line, wraps\nmarkdown at a hardcoded 80 columns (squishing wide terminals), and offers no\nline numbers or line-addressed navigation in the pager. Four improvements:\n\n1. Render the non-raw header as an aligned key/value table.\n2. Honor the terminal width when rendering markdown instead of squishing at 80.\n3. Show a line-number gutter in the interactive pager (fancy/non-raw mode).\n4. Support vim-style jumps: `\u003cn\u003eg` (go to body line *n*), `gg` (top), `G` (bottom).\n\nOut of scope: live re-flow on terminal resize (the pager already does not\nre-wrap pre-rendered content); line numbers in piped/`--no-pager` output;\nline numbers in raw mode.\n\n## Affected files\n\n- `internal/render/render.go` — `ShowHeader`, `RenderBody`, `Show`, `ShowOptions`.\n- `internal/render/render_test.go` — header + width assertions.\n- `cmd/kref/commands.go` — `newShowCmd` (width detection, pager assembly, Tracked note).\n- `cmd/kref/pager.go` — gutter rendering, vim navigation, `Page` signature.\n- `cmd/kref/pager_test.go` — new; navigation + gutter tests.\n\nNo new dependencies (`lipgloss`, `bubbles`, `glamour`, `x/term` already present).\n\n## 1. Header as an aligned key/value table\n\n`ShowHeader` emits aligned rows instead of the inline\n`\u003cid\u003e [tier/status] \u003ctitle\u003e — by \u003cauthor\u003e \u003cemail\u003e` line. Label column is padded\nto the widest present label; a horizontal rule closes the block.\n\n```\nID       \u003cfull-id\u003e\nStatus   \u003ctier-badge\u003e / \u003cstatus\u003e\nTitle    \u003ctitle\u003e\nAuthor   \u003ccreatedBy\u003e \u003ccreatedByEmail\u003e\nLabels   l1, l2                              (row present only when labels exist)\nMerged   ◆ merged — concurrent edits …       (row present only when snap.Merged)\nOrigin   \u003ctrigger\u003e by \u003cactor\u003e (\u003cactorKind\u003e) [from \u003csourcePath\u003e]   (one row per provenance entry)\nTracked  \u003ctrackedPath\u003e [\u003cdrift\u003e]             (row present only when tracked)\n─────────────────────────────────────────\n```\n\nDetails:\n\n- **Full ID** is retained (Show is the canonical reference surface — existing\n  comment in `render.go`).\n- **Status row** value is `Tier(snap.Tier, color) + \" / \" + snap.Status`\n  (glyph + tier word + status), preserving the colored tier badge.\n- **Tracked moves into the header** from its current trailing position after the\n  body. Drift is computed in the command layer (`bridge.DriftState`) and passed\n  into the header via a new `ShowOptions.TrackedNote` field, so the `render`\n  package keeps no dependency on `bridge`. `TrackedNote` is the preformatted\n  string `\"\u003cpath\u003e [\u003cdrift\u003e]\"`; empty ⇒ no Tracked row.\n- **Rule width** = the widest visible header row, measured with `lipgloss.Width`\n  (ANSI-aware), so the rule never overflows and never depends on terminal width.\n- **Determinism:** color off ⇒ no ANSI ⇒ stable output for tests. The tier badge\n  is the only colored cell.\n\n`ShowHeader` signature becomes\n`ShowHeader(w io.Writer, snap *entry.Snapshot, color bool, trackedNote string)`.\n`Show` passes `opts.TrackedNote`; the pager path calls `ShowHeader` directly.\n\n## 2. Honor terminal width\n\n- Width detected once in `newShowCmd` via `term.GetSize(int(os.Stdout.Fd()))`;\n  fallback `80` when not a TTY or on error, floor of `1`.\n- `ShowOptions` gains `Width int` (0 ⇒ no wrap / current behavior).\n- `RenderBody` gains a `width int` parameter:\n  - `width \u003e 0` and markdown ⇒ render through\n    `glamour.NewTermRenderer(\u003cstyle\u003e, glamour.WithWordWrap(width))` where\n    `\u003cstyle\u003e` is the dark standard style when `color`, else `plainMarkdownStyle`.\n    (Verify the exact glamour v1.0.0 option for selecting the dark standard\n    style — `WithStandardStyle`/`WithStylePath`/`WithAutoStyle` — against source\n    before coding; assume-hallucination rule.)\n  - `width == 0` ⇒ current behavior unchanged (color: `glamour.Render(body,\"dark\")`;\n    plain: `WithWordWrap(0)`).\n- Command sets `opts.Width = detectedWidth` when stdout is a TTY (covers\n  `--no-pager` on a terminal too), `0` when piped. The pager path passes\n  `W − gutter` (see §3).\n- All other `RenderBody`/`Show`/`ShowHeader` callers updated for the new\n  signatures.\n\n## 3. Line-number gutter (pager + fancy only)\n\nThe gutter is **presentation-only**. The pager model keeps `m.lines` as the raw\nheader++body split (so search line indices are unchanged); the gutter is applied\nwhen building the viewport content.\n\n- Header lines render a blank gutter: `strings.Repeat(\" \", d) + \" │ \"`.\n- Body lines render a right-aligned number: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%*d │ \", d, n)` where\n  `n` is the 1-based displayed body-line number and `d = digits(bodyLineCount)`.\n- Gutter total width `gutterW = d + 3` (the ` │ ` is space-bar-space).\n- Body markdown is wrapped to `W − gutterW` via a **bounded two-pass**:\n  1. Render body at width `W`; count display lines `n0`; `d = digits(n0)`.\n  2. Render body at `W − (d+3)`; count `n1`. If `digits(n1) != d`, set\n     `d = digits(n1)` and render once more. Bounded to ≤ 4 iterations, then\n     accept (digit count is monotonic in narrowing and converges immediately in\n     practice). A clear comment documents the convergence.\n- **Raw mode**: no gutter, no width wrap (verbatim body).\n- The gutter applies only in the interactive pager; piped/`--no-pager` output is\n  never numbered.\n\n## 4. Vim navigation\n\nNew `pagerModel` state: `numBuf string`, `gPending bool`.\n\nNon-search key handling:\n\n- `0`–`9`: append to `numBuf`; do not forward to the viewport (digits must not\n  scroll). Footer shows the pending count (vim-style).\n- `g`:\n  - `numBuf != \"\"` ⇒ jump to body line `atoi(numBuf)` clamped to\n    `[1, bodyCount]`; `SetYOffset(bodyStart + n − 1)`; clear `numBuf`, `gPending`.\n  - else if `gPending` ⇒ `GotoTop`; clear `gPending`.\n  - else ⇒ set `gPending = true`.\n- `G`, `end` ⇒ `GotoBottom`; clear `numBuf`, `gPending`.\n- `home` ⇒ `GotoTop`; clear state.\n- Any other key ⇒ clear `numBuf` and `gPending`, then fall through to the\n  viewport update (so a stray prefix never lingers).\n\n`bodyStart` = number of header lines (= `len(header)`); jumps and numbering are\nbody-relative and work in raw mode too (just unnumbered). The old combined\n`case \"g\", \"home\": GotoTop` is removed. Footer help text updated to list\n`\u003cn\u003eg`, `gg/G`.\n\n`Page` signature changes to carry the split + gutter, e.g.:\n\n```go\ntype pagerContent struct {\n    title   string\n    header  []string // un-numbered lines (may be empty)\n    body    []string // numbered lines when number == true\n    number  bool     // show the line-number gutter\n    gutterW int      // total gutter width; 0 when number == false\n}\nfunc Page(pc pagerContent) error\n```\n\n`newPagerModel` stores `lines = header ++ body`, `bodyStart = len(header)`,\n`bodyCount = len(body)`, `number`, `gutterW`. `View`/`SetContent` apply the\ngutter; `searchMatches` and jumps operate on `m.lines` (raw).\n\n## 5. Command assembly (`newShowCmd`)\n\n```\nwidth := ttyWidth(cmd)                 // 0 when not a TTY\ntrackedNote := \"\"\nif snap.Tracked { trackedNote = snap.TrackedPath + \" [\" + drift + \"]\" }\nopts := render.ShowOptions{Raw: raw, NoHeader: noHeader, Color: useColor(cmd),\n                           Width: width, TrackedNote: trackedNote}\n\nif usePager(cmd) \u0026\u0026 !noPager {\n    header := \u003cShowHeader to buffer, split to lines\u003e (empty when noHeader)\n    if raw {\n        body := split(snap.Body); number := false; gutterW := 0\n    } else {\n        body, gutterW := renderPagerBody(snap, color, width)  // two-pass §3\n        number := true\n    }\n    return Page(pagerContent{title, header, body, number, gutterW})\n}\n// non-pager: unchanged path, but Tracked now comes from the header (no trailing append)\nvar buf bytes.Buffer\nrender.Show(\u0026buf, snap, opts)\nfmt.Fprint(cmd.OutOrStdout(), buf.String())\n```\n\nThe current trailing `Tracked:` append in `newShowCmd` is removed (now a header row).\n\n## Testing (TDD)\n\n- `internal/render/render_test.go`:\n  - Rewrite header assertions for the aligned table (ID, Status, Title, Author,\n    Labels, Origin, Merged, Tracked rows; negative cases for absent rows).\n  - `RenderBody` width: a long markdown paragraph wraps at the given width\n    (no line exceeds it) when `width\u003e0`; `width==0` preserves current no-wrap.\n- `cmd/kref/pager_test.go` (new): construct `pagerModel`, send `tea.KeyMsg`s:\n  - `5`,`g` ⇒ `YOffset == bodyStart + 4`; clamp beyond `bodyCount`.\n  - `g`,`g` ⇒ top; `G` ⇒ bottom.\n  - Gutter: header lines blank gutter, body lines numbered, search indices map\n    to raw `m.lines`.\n- Run via `task test` (wires `KREF_GITLEAKS`); never bare `go test ./...`.\n\n## Risks / judgment calls\n\n- **Tracked relocation** into the header (user-approved).\n- **glamour dark-style option name** must be verified against installed source.\n- **Two-pass gutter** is the minimum needed to satisfy width + numbering\n  together; bounded and commented to avoid over-engineering concerns."}]}